From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: slothfulchat <dev@slothfulchat.local>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:07:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 27/28] web-app: render animated Lottie (.tgs) stickers with
 lottie-web

Telegram animated stickers (.tgs = gzipped Lottie JSON) can't be shown by an
<img>. Add a LottieSticker component that fetches the blob, gunzips .tgs via
DecompressionStream (with a compressed + decompressed size cap so a hostile
sticker can't gzip-bomb the tab), and plays it with lottie-web's eval-free
'light' player (required by the app CSP: no 'unsafe-eval'), honoring
prefers-reduced-motion and remounting per file via a key. messageAttachment
routes .tgs stickers to it and keeps static/webp on the existing <img> path.
The component takes an optional className so the composer picker can reuse it.
Mirrors ArcaneChat's Android LottieDecoder; the core carries the blob and never
renders it.
